text: Events from the year 1516 in Ireland. ==Events== The Book of Fenagh is a manuscript of prose and poetry written in Classical Irish by Muirgheas mac Pháidín Ó Maolconaire in the monastery at Fenagh, County Leitrim. It was commissioned by Tadhg O'Roddy, the coarb of the monastery, and is believed to derive from the "old Book of Caillín" (), a lost work about Caillín, founder of the monastery. Ó Maolconaire began work about 1516. ==Births== ==Deaths== ==References== Category:1510s in Ireland Ireland Category:Years of the 16th century in Ireland
